Re: Can I use "no hou ga" when I compare several things?
by Svensk » Tue 06.30.2009 10:27 am One more question!In the sentence "Kyoto to Sapporo to Sendai no naka de, doko ga ichiban tabemono ga oishii desu ka" you find the word "Ichiban" before the noun "tabemono", which is kind of confusing, since "Ichiban" means "most, -est". Should'nt it be infront of "oishii"?
