Re: Can I use "no hou ga" when I compare several things?
by Ryouka » Tue 06.30.2009 11:14 am With where it is it asks where has the best food that is delicious, rather than the most delicious food. I honestly can't say I've ever heard it said before, but I haven't heard a whole ton of conversational Japanese.
